title: Ukhu Qhata
text: Ukhu Qhata (<a href="Quechua%20language">Quechua</a> "ukhu" deep, "qhata" slope, hillside, "deep slope", Hispanicized spelling "Ojocata") is a mountain in the <a href="Paryaqaqa%20mountain%20range">Paryaqaqa</a> mountain range in the <a href="Andes">Andes</a> of <a href="Peru">Peru</a>, about high. It is situated in the <a href="Jun%C3%ADn%20Region">Junín Region</a>, <a href="Yauli%20Province">Yauli Province</a>, <a href="Suitucancha%20District">Suitucancha District</a>. Ukhu Qhata lies south-east of the mountains <a href="Putka%20%28Jun%C3%ADn%29">Putka</a> and <a href="Qarwachuku">Qarwachuku</a>, west of the mountain <a href="Wallakancha">Wallakancha</a> and north-east of the mountain <a href="Wayllakancha">Wayllakancha</a>.
